--- Information Theory ---
  H(c7) = 6.3322 bits
  H(c7 | lambda) = 0.0005 bits
  I(lambda; c7) = 6.3317 bits = 99.99% of H(c7)
  => Lambda captures 99.99% of c7 information
  => The non-measurable residual is 0.01% = 0.0005 bits

  For comparison:
  I(scores; c7) = 3.4854 bits = 55.04% of H(c7)
